      "bio": "Bex McCharen (they/them) is an interdisciplinary artist, fashion designer, and founder of the inclusive fashion label Chromat. Their practice spans quilting, cyanotype, photography, social practice, and inclusive design. They are based in Miami and are currently an artist in residence at Oolite Arts and the Miami Cancer Institute. McCharen was awarded the Smithsonian National Design Award, recognized in Forbes 30 Under 30 and OUT100, and has collaborated with Beyoncé, Intel, Disney, and Reebok. They gave a TED Talk on inclusive design and have spoken at SXSW, Harvard, Parsons, MIT, and Tulane. McCharen curated Queer Joy at MoMA PS1 and their work has been exhibited at the Metropolitan Museum of Art."
